Example:

    $.ajax({   
         method: &quot;POST&quot;,
         url: &quot;script.php&quot;,
         data: {team: team}
    });

Your PHP code should be:

    &lt;?php
    if(isset($_POST[&#39;team&#39;])){
      $team = $_POST[&#39;team&#39;];
      echo $team;
    }
    else {
      echo &#39;failed&#39;;
    }

You don&#39;t need to 

    include_once &quot;script.php&quot;;

in order to be able to send an AJAX request to it. Instead of

    $team = team; //incorrect

you need

    $team = $_POST[&quot;team&quot;];

in your AJAX request change

    data: team

into

    data: {team: team}

